		<div id="comment_body_65542850"><p>Step counting is pretty unreliable in general. I've worked with research step counters, expensive things dedicated to the purpose, and you still get people (recovering from surgery) that apparently walk 50k steps per day. Distance covered is better, but GPS is the best way to measure it and it doesn't work so well inside. Moving time is pretty good though, and can be measured fairly reliably.</p><p>But step counting is easier to gamify.</p></div>
	</div>

