	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65541958"><p>You are way overthinking it.  Japanese numbers use powers of ten up to 10,000 and then switch to powers of 10,000.  1,000,000 is called "100 man" (a hundred 10,000-unit counts) and the next largest value with its own name is 100,000,000 (one "oku").  That's why they settled on 10,000 as the nice round number.</p></div>
	</div>

