	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65542206"><p>I'm sure this is already known but the absolute count is way way secondary to frequency.  If you do 20 minutes of activity and are sedentary the rest of the day, this is far worse for metabolism and health than 2 minutes of activity every hour.</p><p>The only thing a higher number of steps proves is that your frequency probably has to be higher to get there.</p></div>
	</div>

